Entry 4
Date: 2026-03-08
Entry Type: Bug Fix
Task Worked On: "clear" function, making sure it deleted all nodes
Issue Or Decision: When I tried deleing nodes in the list, the program would crash
since the list was circular and the tailNode->nextNode points to the headNode
which leads to the nullptr being hit. This means that it would continue to delete
memory.
Error: Program would crash/looped when "clear" was called.
What I tried: Went through looping/deleting nodes with while(currentNode!=nullptr)
but the last node points back to the head and not nulltr, the loop didn't stop.
Fix: Broke the first cycle with tailnode->nextNode=nullptr which made the circular list
into a normal linked list for a second which makes the loop stop at nullptr.
Commits: Repaired clear function by breaking the circular link before nodes were deleted.


